I want to work with children and families. I want to help children who have been hurt. I want to help families who are having problems. I will work for the Division of Family and Children Services. I think social work is a good way to help people. 

I like to help others. In school, I saw people with problems. Some people did not want to talk about their problems. Some people used bad ways to deal with their problems. I wanted to help. I went to college and got a degree in Psychology. After college, I took a break. One day, I met a boy. He was sixteen years old. He was scared. His parents were hurting him.  I wanted to help. I talked to the police. I told them about the boy. The police talked to the boy's parents. I think the parents were not good to the boy. I think the boy needed help. After this, I knew I wanted to be a social worker. I want to help children like this boy.

Social work is about helping people. It is about being fair to everyone. We say that each person is special. But we also want everyone to be the same. I do not like to be the same as everyone else. In school, I showed that I cared about fairness. I did things to show that I was different. I wore my hair in different colors. I wore clothes that I liked. I pierced my ears. I joined a group that helps gay, straight, and bisexual people. I fought against unfairness. I will always fight for fairness.

This paper talks about two ways to look at insomnia: the biological model and the sociocultural model. The biological model looks at genes and how the body works. The sociocultural model looks at how things like where a person lives, their race, and their job can affect sleep. 

This paper will look at studies that show how these models explain insomnia. It will also talk about the good and bad parts of each study.


Insomnia is a sleep problem. It can be caused by many things. Sometimes, it is caused by another mental health problem. Other times, it is caused by a medical problem or by taking medicine.

There are different types of sleep problems. Some common ones are insomnia, hypersomnia (sleeping too much), narcolepsy (falling asleep suddenly), and sleep apnea (breathing problems while sleeping).

This paper will focus on insomnia and how the biological and sociocultural models can explain it.

The biological model looks at how genes and the body work together to cause insomnia.

One study looked at mice. Scientists found that special cells in the mouse brain control sleep and wakefulness. These cells have special parts that can be turned on or off. When scientists turned on these parts, the mice slept more.

This study shows that genes and the body can affect sleep.


The sociocultural model looks at how things like where a person lives, their race, and their job can affect sleep.  This can mean that genetics and the environment work together to cause insomnia. People with certain genes might be more likely to have insomnia if they live in a stressful environment.

This paper talk about three things about Central Auditory Processing Disorder (CAPD). First, it give a short meaning of the disorder. Next, it explain how doctors find out if someone has CAPD. Finally, the paper end with ways a teacher can help a student with CAPD in a regular class.

Central Auditory Processing Disorder (CAPD), also known as Auditory Processing Disorder (APD), means how well the brain use sound.  The brain take in sound and make sense of it. CAPD is when the brain have trouble doing this. People with CAPD can hear sounds, but the brain does not understand the sounds well.

People first talk about CAPD in the 1950s. They called it “auditory imperception”. Doctors started to look for tests to help find children with this problem. 

CAPD can show up in many ways. A person with CAPD may have trouble hearing sounds from different directions. They may find it hard to tell two sounds apart. They may not be able to hear patterns in sounds. They may not understand changes in a person’s voice. One sound may block out another. They may have trouble putting sound clues together to make meaning. They may not be able to tell the order of sounds.

To find out if someone has CAPD, doctors watch how they listen and give them tests. Audiologists, speech therapists, and psychologists can do these tests. There is no one test for CAPD. Doctors use many different tests. Some tests show a person pictures or sounds and ask them to tell what they see or hear. Other tests look at how the brain reacts to sounds.

The play Twelfth Night shows us that disguise can be good for tricks. But in the end, a person must choose to be themself again or lose who they are. 

Ending a trick can be hard because people might get mad. Some people will not care, but others will be hurt.

Disguise about gender is hard because it asks why someone wants to pretend to be the other gender. 

Viola hides as a man to be safe. "I will bring you to a captain in this town/ Where lie my maiden weeds, by whose gentle help/ I was preserved to serve this noble count…” (5.1.247-249)

She is safe, but she misses women friends and support.  She is so good at being a man that Olivia thinks she is Sebastian and falls in love. "Whither, my lord? Cesario, husband, stay." (5.1.138) 

Viola also has feelings for Orsino. "Boy, thou hast said to me a thousand times/ Thou never shouldst love woman like to me.” (5.1. 260-261)

Twelfth Night shows how tricks can help people see their feelings. 

Maybe Olivia likes Cesario because he looks like a man. Or maybe Olivia has secret feelings for women. Shakespeare might be making fun of people who only judge by looks.  

Olivia changes her feelings easily. She likes Cesario, then Sebastian, then sees Viola as a sister. "A sister, you are she." (5.1.315)

German leaders ruled African lands. Some people say this rule was bad and mean. This is true for the Ovaherero and Nama people in South West Africa. 
German rule had many parts. It was not all the same. Some places had good schools.  Britain took over German East Africa in 1919.  They found many Africans who could read and write. 
German leaders also helped schools in places like Kamerun. South West Africa was different. The government did not make many schools.  Mission groups ran most schools, and they did not get much help.  The German leaders did help schools for white people. They made schools and helped groups that teach. This made a big difference for the people of South West Africa. 

Other German places had many people who could read and write. But in South West Africa, most people could not.  There are many reasons why this was. This paper looks at the reasons. It looks at what people who lived there thought about Africans.

Many books talk about schools in German places. Most books are in German and from a long time ago. They show what schools were like. Later books help us compare schools in different places. They also look at parts of schools in more detail. We can see that schools were very different in each place. One book looks at schools in South West Africa and East Africa. It says that the many white people in South West Africa made the schools different.

South West Africa had good weather, but much of it is desert. Many white people lived there. By 1913, more than 15,000 white people lived there. That was more than any other German place.

Popular music has many types of music. It has changed a lot in the last 100 years. There are so many types of music that it is hard to list them all.  Most types of music have smaller types too.  

Heavy Metal rock is one of the most popular types of music today. It is very loud and has strong feelings, mostly sad feelings.

Heavy metal started about 40 years ago. People liked it because it was different.

Today, there are many different types of heavy metal. It is hard to say what heavy metal really is. It took ideas from many other types of music.

To understand heavy metal, we need to know where it came from. 

Heavy metal is about darkness. It is loud, with strong music and strong feelings. People who play heavy metal are very good musicians.

Heavy metal also uses drugs. In the 1970s, people used a lot of drugs. They made music that sounded strange because of the drugs. 

Heavy metal music is dark and strong. This was new in the music world because most popular music was not dark.

Heavy metal also took ideas from a time long ago called the Romantic Era. This time had a lot of dark feelings in the music.


Heavy metal songs often have dark words. Here is an example:

 
[Helter Skelter] by the Beatles is an example of a dark song. It sounds up and down, like the feeling of being on drugs. Some people think this song was one of the first heavy metal songs.

Long ago, before artists like the Surrealists painted their strange pictures, a painter named Henri Rousseau made his own dreams, both in his art and in his life. The painting "The Dream," made in 1910, shows a woman looking at the wonders of a dream. It also shows Rousseau's own dreams of being a good artist. He wanted other people to like his art. But he also wanted to be different and paint his own way. This made him sad.

Rousseau was born in France in 1844. He did not go to art school. He worked for the government until he was forty years old. He was sad after his wife and many children died. He started painting to make himself feel better.

Rousseau wanted to be a famous artist. But he was not like other artists at the time. They were young and famous. He was older and not well-known. He wanted to paint in a way that people would like. But he also wanted to be unique.

A writer named Jan Gordon said that Rousseau wanted to paint in a way that made people think he was a good artist. But Matisse, another artist, wanted to paint in a new way.

Rousseau's painting "The Dream" shows his struggle. He wanted to be accepted. But he also wanted to be himself.

Many people think that good things in life, like art and morals, are close. They are both about what is good and right. A famous writer, John Keats, said, "Beauty is truth, truth beauty." This means that they are the same thing.

We learn many things in school and life. But we seem to know what is good and beautiful without being taught. Art and morals are like explanations, not rules. We try to understand why something is beautiful or good, not how to make it.

We can talk about art or morals, but we can't fully explain them. For example, we can talk about the colors and shapes in a painting, but that does not explain why it is good art. People often say, "There's just something about it," when they like a work of art.

Art and morals are more than just descriptions. They have something special that we cannot fully explain. A writer, Flannery O'Connor, said, "A story is a way to say something that can't be said any other way."

Ethics, or morals, is also like this. We can talk about rules and ideas, but there is a deeper meaning that we feel.

Art and morals touch us in a deep way. They make us feel things that we can't always explain. Literature, especially, is about values. It shows us what is important in life.

Germany is a strong country today. It has its own culture. This culture can be seen from the mountains of Munich to the sea city of Kiel. 

The people of Germany share a unique culture. This culture comes from many tribes. Germany was once called Germania. 

The name Germania comes from a group of people called the Tungrians. Historians are not sure if this is correct. Julius Caesar was the first to use the word "Germanus". He used it to talk about groups of people who lived beyond the Rhine. These people fought against the Romans. Caesar took the word from the Gauls, who also lived near the Rhine.

Some people think the name Germania means "spear". Others think it means "loud" or "noisy". 

The Roman writer Tacitus wrote about Germania. He said that the Germans were a strong, independent people. They did not mix with other groups. Tacitus said that no one would want to leave a good place like Rome to live in Germany. 

In the first century, Germanic tribes lived near the Roman Empire. They traded with the Romans and some even fought for Rome. The Romans did not want to live in Germany. They would send soldiers there to get goods and fight battles. But they mostly stayed in their own empire.

I look down. I see a thing. My brain works. It sees. It thinks. But it does not feel. Like a machine, my mind looks at the thing. It is a bowl. It is brown.

I read a book about art. It said to look at one thing. Only one thing. See the bowl. Not the room. Not the table. Just the bowl.

I want to be an artist. I want to paint. A great artist like Picasso. But I am not great.

I touch the thing. I want to make art. This is my art. I flush the water. The water swirls.

The brown thing does not move. I flush again. It is stuck. I use a mop. I wear a green tie. I am not happy. 

I wipe my hands. I look at the brown thing. It is bad. I want to go home.

Teenagers are hurt and die when they drive. Many things cause this. The National Institutes of Health say that teen brains are not ready for driving.  Teens are also not experienced drivers. This means they have more accidents. They also speed more and drive off the road.

Teens are more likely to have accidents when they drive with friends. Everyone knows teens like to drive with friends. A study in California found a link between the age of the passenger and the number of accidents.

Some states have tried to help. They have rules for new drivers. These rules limit the time teens can drive and who they can drive with.
But these rules are not enough. The problem is that young drivers are not ready for the danger of driving. A psychologist named Marvin Zuckerman says 18 is too young to get a driver’s license. He says teens want to take risks. It is better to wait until they are older.

If we do not change the rules, many more teens will die. More teens will be driving soon. We need to stop young teens from driving.

There is a simple way to do this. Schools can teach teens about driving, but no one under 18 can drive. Teens can get a permit before they get a license. They must also practice driving with an adult.

All states should have the same rules about driving. This will help keep teens safe.

I looked at old films by Thomas Edison. I watched fifteen trick films made between 1895 and 1901. These films use tricks to show things that are not real. My study looked at how these films are made and how they changed over time. 

Most trick films are made in a small space. The camera does not move. The actors stay in one place and move side-to-side. They never walk towards or away from the camera. 

For example, in the film "Uncle Josh in a Spooky Hotel" (1900), the actors move back and forth. They do not go in or out of the view of the camera.


The camera does not move because it is in a small space called a proscenium. This is like a stage. The camera stays in one place, just like a stage actor.

Most trick films use long shots and sometimes medium shots. They never use close-ups. This is because the audience is supposed to see the whole scene at once, just like in a play.

Most trick films are short. They are about one minute long. They show simple tricks, like magic tricks or making things disappear. They do not tell a long story.


Sometimes, a trick film that looks like one shot is actually many shots put together. For example, in "The Execution of Mary, Queen of Scots" (1895), the film looks like one shot but it is really many shots joined together.

John Taylor from Caroline was a strong supporter of Republican ideas. He was mainly a farmer, but his work as a farmer and his short time in politics made him known for his strong belief in personal freedom and his willingness to speak his mind.  His belief in farming was the basis for most of his ideas about how the government should work. He wanted to protect and encourage farming because he thought it was the best job. This belief shaped his ideas about the government's power, the Constitution, and even the courts.

John Taylor believed that the United States had a good chance to make a perfect system because there were no old ideas to get in the way. This meant the country could create a government that worked for the people. He strongly believed in the natural rights of people, and he thought that all these rights are connected. If one is taken away, they all become weaker. These rights should be protected from the government. He said that what some call the "state of nature" meant that strong people with bad intentions would be the most successful. But in a society, this shouldn't be true.

To create a good society, Taylor believed that the government had to understand the good and bad parts of people. Taylor was very firm in his belief that people are both good and bad. He said, "As government is exercised by man, all its virtues and vices must be human." He thought good government protected private property, helped farming, and stopped businesses from becoming too powerful. He believed that a government with good ideas would work well no matter who was in charge, even if those people were greedy. He believed that people are always looking out for themselves, but this was only bad when it meant some people were better off at the expense of others.  A good government was needed to control people's bad parts, and even then it had to be watched carefully so it didn't become bad itself.

Taylor, like many other strong Republicans at the time, believed the Constitution should be followed strictly. He wanted a small federal government with only the powers that were clearly stated in the Constitution. He knew a large federal government would be expensive and could become too powerful. But he also thought that a simple, word-for-word interpretation was dangerous. Without understanding the writers' intentions, this could lead to problems. He even believed that the Declaration of Independence was the real guide for the United States because it talked more about the country as a group of independent states rather than one nation.

Figure 17 shows that the number of commuter logs went down a lot in the third month. This was sad news. It is hard to know why this happened. It could be that winter came to the school and fewer people biked or walked to work. December is also the end of the school year. People are busy with schoolwork and grades. They may not have had time to fill out the log. Also, December is the start of the holiday season. Students and teachers have a long break. They may not need to come to school. Classes start again in late January, which may explain why there were so few logs in that month. But this does not explain why there were so few logs in February. 

It is possible that projects like this have a lot of energy at the start, then the energy goes down. To keep people interested, we had a special week called the Carpool Challenge. This helped to increase the number of logs in March. 

We found that it is hard to keep people interested in a project, especially during holiday breaks and school breaks. 

Another problem is that people like to drive. It is very common in our culture.  To get people to try other ways to get to school, we gave out prizes. We gave gift certificates to restaurants, coffee shops, and stores. It would have been interesting to see if bigger prizes, like a bike, a hybrid car, or an electric car, would have helped more.

We did not change the prizes during the project. It would have been good to make the prizes bigger over time. We could have announced new prizes, like bikes in December and a hybrid or electric car in January. This might have helped people stay interested.

An ETF is a type of investment. It tracks a group of things, like stocks or goods. It is like a basket of investments. You can buy and sell ETFs on the stock market, just like you can buy and sell individual stocks.

ETFs have some good things. They are spread out, so you don't risk all your money on one thing.  They are also cheaper to own than some other types of investments. 

But ETFs also have some downsides. You have to pay a fee each time you buy or sell one. 

There are many different kinds of ETFs. You can find ETFs that track many different things.

This report looks at one ETF called IHF. It compares IHF to the top ten investments inside IHF. We want to know if it is better to own the whole ETF or to own just the top ten investments. 

The top ten investments make up most of IHF. We will look at how good these ten investments are at making money. We will also look at how risky they are.

We will see if it is better to own the ETF or to own just the top ten investments. We will use a tool called "Beta" to measure risk. We will also look at how much money the investments make.

"Dream-Land" is one of Poe's good poems. Poe uses the word "Thule" in his poem.  A long time ago, a writer named Virgil used this word. Virgil wrote about an island far north.  People thought this was the edge of the world.  Poe liked to read German writers.  A writer named Karl Arndt thinks Poe copied a poem by a German writer named Goethe. 
Goethe wrote a famous play called "Faust."  There is a poem in "Faust" called "The King of Thule." This poem is about a king. His wife dies. He drinks too much and is sad. He wants to die. He gives his things away and then throws a cup into the ocean. He closes his eyes and dies.  The king in "The King of Thule" is sad like the speaker in "Dream-Land."
Poe used the word "Thule" twice in his writing. He used it in "Dream-Land" at the beginning and the end of the poem.  The two poems, "The King of Thule" and "Dream-Land," are similar. The speaker in "Dream-Land" talks about a dark and lonely place. He is sad and sees dead friends.  Goethe's poem is also about sadness and loss. 
Goethe was a famous writer. Poe probably knew about him because he liked another writer named Tennyson. Poe said he liked Tennyson.  Poe probably also read Goethe's work because many copies of his books were made.

A customer fell in a store. She hurt her back. The customer wants money from the store. The money is for punishment.

In California, a judge will not throw away the case right away. To get punishment money, the customer must show the store manager did something very bad on purpose. The manager knew about spilled applesauce. He did not clean it up. This is bad.

The customer can say the manager knew this was dangerous. Other people fell before. The manager did not care. This is bad.

The manager said he was eating dinner. He did not have time. Another worker told him too. He said the same thing.

Later, the customer fell. She hurt her back.  The manager did not clean the spill.

California law says you can get punishment money if someone was mean or did not care. The manager may have been mean. He did not care about people slipping.

Four years ago, I took a class about Islam at CBC. We talked a lot about if Islam is a bad religion. This is still a big question today. Since 9/11, the news has changed how it shows Islam. It went from being very mean to Islam to being very nice to it. I do not think anyone could have been president with a name like Barack Obama in 2001. He is Muslim.

The story of Muhammad is interesting. I thought he forced people to be Muslim. I thought he took over tribes and made them follow Islam. But the story makes him look like a good person who was misunderstood. People came to him after seeing his good ways.

There are things in Jesus's story and Muhammad's story that are similar. One example is when Muhammad took food and made it grow so there was enough for forty men. This makes Muhammad look like a good person who did not need to show off. It is like they are trying to make him look like Jesus.

There are many stories in the book about how people became Muslim. But some of these stories come from people who heard them from other people. This makes the stories seem less true.

I think the worst part is that the book tries to make Muhammad look like a good, kind, and wise person. But history says that Muhammad was not like that. I wonder if people who follow Islam today know the real story about Muhammad.

Jesus' ideas change after he die.  Christianity grow far from its start.  The world is more aware now and want things to change.  Some people like old things and want no change.  But they may not have much power.  More and more Christians will want to know what Jesus really said.  They will want to know what was added later. This may take time, but it will happen.  Christianity will go back to its start.

People will take away the extra ideas, like turning back a clock.  Only Jesus' ideas will be left.  This will happen in America and Europe.  Many people will worship like it is Jesus' time.  The church will be strong, but people will believe the same things.  They will not argue as much.

History shows big changes.  Christians were hurt by the Roman people, but later Rome became Christian.  America changed from slavery to African-Americans in leadership.  Christianity will change too.  It will go back to its start.

A part of this will be seeing Jesus' words as symbols, not just plain words.

What happened since Jesus?  Long ago, there was only Judaism.  Judaism is the start of Christianity.  Judaism had one God, holy books, and people believed in God's message.  When Rome took over, there were many different groups of Jews.

The book "The Jungle" shows people can be very selfish. They care only about themselves and making their lives better. They do not care about people who are less lucky. The book shows this in many ways. 

The owners of big factories only want to make more money and power. They do not care if people or the environment get hurt.  The book says, "The line of the buildings stood clear-cut and black against the sky; here and there out of the mass rose the great chimneys, with the river of smoke streaming away to the end of the world." This shows how much pollution the factories make. The owners do not care about the people or animals that are hurt by the pollution.

The owners also do not care about the workers in their factories. They want to save money and make more.  They force workers to work long hours and then fire them without warning. The workers have no protection from the bosses. The bosses can treat them badly because there are no laws to stop them.  The book says, "So from the top to bottom the place is simply a seething cauldron of jealousies and hatreds; there is no loyalty or decency anywhere about it, there is no place in it where a man counted for anything against a dollar."

The workers are treated like slaves. They have no way to leave the bad conditions. The book says, "Here is a population, low-class and mostly foreign, hanging always on the verge of starvation and dependent for its opportunities of life upon the whim of men every bit as brutal and unscrupulous as the old-time slave drivers; under such circumstances, immorality is exactly as inevitable, and as prevalent, as it is under the system of chattel slavery."

Many writers use ways to make readers feel a certain way about things. Some ways are better than others. F. Scott Fitzgerald uses many ways in his book _The Great Gatsby_. Sometimes he uses words together that do not usually go together to make readers feel a certain way. Sometimes he gives meaning to a symbol, then uses it to make readers feel a way.

Fitzgerald uses this last way with many colors, like gold, green, white/gray, and red/pink. In _The Great Gatsby_ he gives meaning to white/gray and red/pink, then uses them to make readers remember a feeling about something important.

The meaning Fitzgerald gives to white/gray is being the same. White is a little nicer and more high class. Gray is older and faded. Fitzgerald shows this meaning at the start of the book with lots of white and gray. Daisy and Jordan are always “in white.” Everyone wears white: Nick wears “white flannels” to Gatsby’s party, Tom wears a “white shirt” when he meets Myrtle, and Catherine is “powdered milky white.” The only time people are not wearing white is when Nick is at Gatsby’s party. He sees “primary colors” (40). Fitzgerald also uses white and gray to show common things. Nick goes “down the white chasms of lower New York” (56), names at Gatsby’s party are “gray names” (61), Catherine’s apartment is “one slice in a long white cake of apartment-houses” — being the same (28). He also describes common people or places as white or gray: Jordan and Daisy had a “white girlhood” (19), there are “gray cars” and “gray land” (23) in the valley of ashes, the “Italian child” in the railroad is “gray” (26), and the dog-seller is “a gray old man” (27).

After Fitzgerald uses these colors a lot, he uses them to show that something is not important or is the same. This using colors to show readers something starts with Daisy. After a long time without using these colors, Fitzgerald describes Daisy as “dressed in white” in “a little white roadster.” Readers start to see Daisy as less of a person, more like something uniform, something Gatsby wants (74). Fitzgerald uses more of this to show Daisy as a uniform person. There is a “gray haze of Daisy’s fur collar” (18), and she is again in a “white” (115) dress before Tom and Gatsby meet.

San Diego area has good farms. The weather is mild and sunny. People grow many foods here, like tomatoes, oranges, green leaves, squash, broccoli, herbs, peaches, lemons, berries, honey, and peppers.  Many people want to buy food from farms that use no chemicals. There are many farms in San Diego that sell food without chemicals. People have to wait a long time to buy this food. Eggs and milk without chemicals are also popular. Many farms give tours. People can also walk and watch birds on the farms. This kind of farm can help the farmer get money from the government. Farms can also help animals and plants.

Organic farms are good for animals and plants. There are more different kinds of plants and animals. There are no chemicals in the soil or water. But, organic farms cost more money to run.  People have to work harder to keep pests and weeds away. They also have to use different ways to help the soil. Sometimes, organic farms lose more food.

Some things help animals but are not part of organic farming.  These things cost more money too. Farmers have to plant special plants, move animals around, and get rid of bad plants. They also have to take care of plants to help animals.


The land we are talking about is near the town of Potrero. It is 160 acres. There are plants called chaparral, grass from another country, and oak trees. The land is near the Cleveland National Forest. The land is part of a plan to protect animals and plants. This plan helps over one hundred kinds of plants and animals. Many are in danger of disappearing, like the Stephens' kangaroo rat and the mountain yellow-legged frog.  

People have lived in this area for a long time.  People raised cows and cut wood here a long time ago. This piece of land was given to someone to farm many years ago.


This is an example of how a small farmer might farm the land. We looked at a real farm in the same area.

Culture is very important in talks. Culture is not easy to explain. It is not all the same. It is not one thing. Saying “all Russians are stubborn” or “all Japanese are good listeners” is too simple. It is better to know how a culture thinks and feels about what is being talked about. When you meet a new culture, you see it like your own culture. You make comparisons.

To understand a new culture, you can learn about its history and its beliefs. You should not judge or try to change it. You must accept it and work with it, especially when you are not in a strong position. If you are in a new place, respect its customs and beliefs. This will help you talk to people and make a deal.

Culture is not just about countries. Companies have their own cultures too. Some companies work long hours, others work short hours. You can see culture in how people dress, how they talk, and how they hire people. Some companies want their workers to help others, others only want them to help the company.

American companies have many different cultures. Some are strict, others are relaxed. This shows that even in one country, there are many different ways to think. Some cultures are not as different as American culture. They look the same on the outside, but you need to look deeper.

Values are important because they show why a culture does things. If a culture values saving face, people will not show anger or shame in a deal. If a culture values hard work, people will not give up easily. You should know these things before you talk to someone. But you should also learn about the person you are talking to.

The saying, "The fool hath said in his heart, 'There is no God,'" is in Psalm 14 of the Bible. This saying is at the start of Saint Anselm's idea about God. Saint Thomas Aquinas also thinks this way. Both men want to prove God exists. To make this easy, we will say both men believe in the God of the Bible. 

We can compare their ideas because they both defend the same God. We will look at their ideas to see which is better. I think neither argument proves God exists completely.

Saint Anselm's idea is about faith. He says we can know God by looking inside ourselves. He says God exists in our minds, so we can't imagine him not existing. He says we don't need proof from the world because God is true in our minds. This is called faith.

Saint Thomas Aquinas thinks we can prove God with reason and things we can see. He says we don't need faith. This would be good for telling people about God because they could believe because of logic. Saint Thomas has five ideas to prove God: change, cause and effect, things happening by chance, things being better or worse, and things working together in harmony. He says each idea shows God is needed. Like if you are missing a puzzle piece, you know it exists because the rest fit together.

A prince was born a long time ago, maybe in the fifth or sixth century BCE. He would become known as Buddha. He left the world and found peace, and his teaching started Buddhism. The oldest part of Buddhism is called Theravada Buddhism. This religion is about two thousand five hundred years old. It is different now than when Buddha lived. You can see this in Sri Lanka, where monks and regular people do a water-cutting ceremony each year. It is important to them, even though Buddha never said to do it. 

Buddhism has changed in many ways, from small traditions to big ideas. This is because of things inside and outside the religion. Some things helped Buddhism, and some things hurt it.

This talk will use some special words. "Inside" means from people who believe in Buddha's teaching, monks or not. "Outside" means from people who don't believe. "Hostile" means something bad that hurts Buddhism. "Benign" means something that doesn't help or hurt.

First, let's look at the basics of Theravada Buddhism. Buddhists believe in the Buddha, the teaching (Dhamma), and the community of followers (Sangha). The Dhamma is like a set of books called the Tripitaka. One part has Buddha's talks, another has rules for monks, and the last part talks about big ideas like no soul (Anatta), suffering (Dukkha), and change (Anicca).  

To end the cycle of life and death (Samsara), you must understand these ideas. You must also stop wanting things (lobha), being angry (dosa), and being confused (moha). This will lead to enlightenment. The rules for monks are in the Vinaya Pitaka and there are many more. The most important idea is the Four Noble Truths.

First, life has suffering (Dukkha). Second, wanting things makes us suffer. Third, suffering can stop. Fourth, there is a way to stop suffering.

The United States and Mexico had a long rivalry. It went on for 57 years, from 1836 to 1893. (Diehl and Goerts 2000 p. 145). The rivalry was at its worst during the Mexican-American War of 1846-1848. In this war, the United States beat Mexico. The United States took Texas and the American Southwest as new land. There were many other fights between the two countries. The rivalry ended just before World War I.

The rivalry started because Americans and Mexicans disagreed on things like religion, culture, and tradition. They also had different wants. This is like many other countries that are neighbors. Countries that share a border often have disagreements that lead to fighting. The United States and Mexico are like many other countries that have fought a lot. David M. Pletcher (1977) said, “Only in Mexico and Cuba can one find long-lasting American problems” (p. 41). Both Mexico and Cuba are close to the United States and have been rivals. Other countries in Latin America have had good relationships with the United States.

Religion was a big problem between the two countries. This is a problem that has happened in many countries. Sally Frahm (2001) said, “If in the twentieth century Americans were against fascism and communism, in the eighteenth and nineteenth they were against Catholicism and monarchy”  (p.86). Like the Cold War between the United States and the Soviet Union, the rivalry between the United States and Mexico was partly about ideas and partly about what each country thought was important. In this case, the disagreements were not about politics but about religion.

The distrust grew from the distrust between the English and the Spanish. The United States and Mexico inherited these feelings from their old rulers. This made it hard to have good relationships. Diehl and Goerts (2000) list 17 problems between Mexico and the United States during the rivalry. Most of these were about land. There were fights about border raids from Mexico into the United States, and other problems on the border.

Border raids by criminals from American towns were a big problem. This went on until both the United States and Mexico sent troops to their borders (Schmitt 1974 p. 97). Schmitt (1974) says that the rivalry started to lessen as “Mexico became clearly dependent on the United States” (p. 109) and ended as American goals “changed from taking land to controlling Mexico’s economy” (p.110) in the late 1800s.

Fifteen years ago, I got sick.  I did not know I was sick. I was a nurse. I worked as a nurse because I wanted to be safe. I thought it would always be a safe job. I wanted to be a scientist or a writer, but I thought nursing was safer.

When I was 46, I could not work anymore.  I was alone. I had no money. I get money from the government, but it is not much.  I still cannot work. My life is hard every day. I worry about money and safety. I need help from my family and friends. They help me. I know I could not live without them.

Bad things happen in life. We cannot always be ready for them.  We need to help each other.

Some people say we should not rely on the government.  They say we should be strong and do things alone. But our history shows that we are strong together. We help each other when we are in trouble. 

We need to be ready for bad things.  I have a kit for emergencies. I have food, water, and tools. But I also talk to my neighbors. We help each other.

Why do living things change over time? Are there limits to how they change?  We know a lot about how animals and plants change, but we still do not know all the ways they change.  Scientists use math to study how living things change. This helps us understand the shapes and forms of living things.

Our study looks at a type of shell. We use math to understand how these shells change over time. We look at how they grow and how they are different from each other.  We use pictures of the shells to find measurements. Then we use a computer program to make new shapes. This helps us see how shells could change.

A shell is like a tube that spins around. It has many parts called whorls.  A whorl is like a circle that is part of the shell. All the whorls are connected by lines called sutures. The biggest whorl is called the body whorl. The rest are called the spire. The top of the spire is called the apex. 

We can look at shells from many different angles. We can look at the top, the bottom, the opening, and the opposite of the opening.

There is a way to count the whorls on a shell. You can look at the shell from the top and find the first line that separates the whorls. Then you can count the whorls. 

Think of a shell like a series of doors that open one by one. Each door is a whorl. We can track how the doors open and how big they are to learn how the shell grew. We can use math to describe this growth.

Indonesia has not had much change in the rate of death for new babies and babies in the last ten years. While the country is close to meeting many goals, like clean water and bathrooms, health for moms and kids is not getting better fast enough to reach the goals by 2015.  This paper will talk about the reasons for this and why Indonesia needs to make its health system stronger.

Indonesia has made some progress in having a doctor or nurse at births. Now, 72% of babies are born with a helper. But, this number includes helpers who are not doctors, like midwives. These helpers cannot help with problems during birth (this is why so many moms die from bleeding). So, the progress is not as good as it looks. Also, fewer sick children are seeing a doctor. We do not have enough information about care after birth, but it is clear that this is also a problem.

Cesarean sections are not as common as they should be, only 4% of births. This also shows a problem. In cities, 7% of babies are born this way, but only 2% in the country. This shows that people in cities get better care. Another problem is that the poor have much less access to healthcare. The poorest people are 27% less likely to use healthcare services. This is likely because they cannot afford it.

To improve care for moms and babies, we need to ask: should Indonesia do special programs, or make the whole health system better? Programs seem easier. They focus on one problem and can get results fast. But, there are problems with this. Spending too much on one program can mean other programs get less money and doctors will only work in the well-funded areas. Also, many programs can do the same thing, which makes things more complicated.

Victorian books have lots of details and talk about the rich people from that time. Two books from that time, "Oliver Twist" and "Wuthering Heights," are different. They are mysteries with strange things that happen, which is not usual for books from that time. These strange things help us understand the characters better.

Here is a part from "Oliver Twist":

“Now, lots of strange ideas filled his mind. He felt like he was still walking with Sikes and Crackit, who were angry and fighting. He could hear their words. Then he looked around and saw he was talking to them…. Suddenly he heard gunshots. There were loud cries and shouts. Lights flashed, and everything was noisy and chaotic, as an unseen hand quickly took him away. Through all these quick images, there was a feeling of pain that never went away, always bothering him.” 

These books often use dreams or dreamlike moments to create mystery. In "Oliver Twist," these strange happenings show us what is going on inside Oliver. We can see his pain and how he understands the bad things happening around him. When Oliver is shot, he remembers it in a dreamlike way while he is trying to find help. This shows that Oliver has no control over what is happening to him. He is very hurt, and he is afraid. He doesn't even notice the person who carries him away. He is too overwhelmed.

The shooting shows us that Oliver has no power over his life. He can't control anything, even when he is in danger.  We also see that Oliver is starting to give up. It seems like Fagin has broken his spirit and made him accept this sadness.  If Oliver was not broken, he would have tried to do something to save himself.


Here is a part from "Wuthering Heights":

“The day passed – but it felt like there was no day. It was gone as soon as it came, and then night came again; night that was long and short. It was long in its scary quiet and short in its quick passing hours."

A few years ago, I worked at an after school program. I helped young students with schoolwork. I was good at helping with English and reading. One boy, Adrian, was having big problems with reading. He was in third or fourth grade. It was hard to help him. Some letters he could read, but others he could not. It was strange. He spoke perfect English, but he had trouble with reading.

One day, Adrian's mother came to the program. She only spoke Spanish. I knew a little Spanish, but not much. We could talk a little. Then I understood. Adrian could read, but he did not know the English alphabet well.

I tell this story because it shows that language can be a big problem in schools. It is not always easy to see the problem. Even if a child speaks English well, reading can be hard.

What can we do? For Adrian, it was simple: more help with reading English. But for children who do not speak English well, it is harder. There is no one answer.  We need to try many things.

One good idea is to teach in two languages. This helps all children, not just those who speak Spanish.

It is good for everyone. Some people worry that this will cost too much money. But that is not true. If we teach in two languages more often, everyone will benefit. 

We do not need all teachers to speak two languages. But we can have helpers who do.

When we are small, many people tell us that there is something big, bigger than us. Some go to church or temple, others look inside. Some people believe the religion they grew up with. Others say there is nothing beyond our world. We may think one way about right and wrong, but then change our minds. We all try to find our own way to understand our place in the world. We look for hope in the darkness.

My father said his favorite bird was a cardinal. We sat on the porch. It rained hard on the roof. The rain made the plants by the porch wet. He looked out at the rain. He seemed sad. He was thinner now. His hair was not as thick. He did not look at me. I felt alone and scared. I did not want to talk about how much I would miss him. If I did, it would feel real. I hugged him and sat closer. We looked at the rain together.

My father died in December. He was sick for a long time. He died five days after my twenty-second birthday. The medicine did not make him feel better, but it kept him alive longer. I did not know why. What kind of God would do this? I did not pray. I did not think God was listening.

I did not want to watch him die. I knew my father better than anyone else. I knew he did not want me to see him die. I wanted to remember him how he was, not how he died.  I stayed in bed for three days. No one called me.

The "Gothic Novel" is old and new. This is what Ian Watt says in his book, "The Rise of the Gothic Novel."  People have said bad things about Gothic stories. They have also said good things about them. Some say Gothic stories are not deep. Others say they are very exciting. The first Gothic novel was "The Castle of Otranto" by Horace Walpole. Walpole used old stories and new ideas to make a new kind of story. He used old ideas from plays and new ideas about nature. He called his story a "Gothic Story." 
The Gothic story uses ideas from old times. It uses ideas from old plays, buildings, and ways of life. Even when "The Castle of Otranto" was first published, the word "Gothic" was used to describe many things. People thought it was old-fashioned and not as good as new things. But the Gothic story is interesting because it combines old ideas with a new way of telling a story.  The reader can see inside the characters' minds. This is why Gothic stories last so long. They seem both old and new.

One important idea in Gothic stories is chivalry. Chivalry was a way to train knights in the Middle Ages.  Gothic writers liked chivalry because it was about courage, honor, and skill.  They thought these things were missing in their own time.  The idea of chivalry is like a dream of a better past.  It is used to make the past seem romantic and special.

Walpole wrote "The Castle of Otranto" during a time of trouble in his country. He was worried about the future. He may have thought that people in the past were better than people now. In his story, we see this idea in the character Frederic. Here is a description of Frederic:


The description of Frederic shows many things that were important for knights in the past. He is a prince, he has been through sadness and loss, and he is thought to have been killed by bad people. The idea of the brave knight is very strong in this story. It is an important part of the Gothic story.

Supply chain management is the way goods move.  Goods move from when a customer orders something to when the customer gets the goods. This includes the raw materials, making the goods, and sending the goods to the customer.  

A man named Keith Oliver first used the words "supply chain management" in 1982.  He said it is about planning, doing, and checking the supply chain to make customers happy quickly and well.

There are six main parts to a supply chain: making things, getting supplies, keeping things in stock, where things are made, moving things, and sharing information.  Business managers use these parts to give good service to customers.

* **Making things** is the first step. It is the start of the whole process.  Managers need to know what customers want. They can look at the market to see what people want.

Once managers know what customers want, they can decide what to make and how much to make. They also need to decide where to make things. The best place will make the most goods well and keep customers happy.

Managers also need to plan how to use the workers and machines. Making things is very important. If things are not planned well, it can cost a lot of time and money.

* **Getting supplies** is the second part. This means choosing the best ways to get the things needed to make the goods.  A company might have many ways to make one product. Each way uses different workers and machines. The manager must choose the best way for each part of making the product.  

A manager might also choose to give some of the work to other companies. This is called outsourcing.  Managers do this to make things faster and cheaper.

Hitler is alive in Burma, the sign says. 

Ellen Page, a famous actress, stands alone. She has a piece of cardboard with words written on it. The words say, "Hitler is alive in Burma." Burma is a country in Southeast Asia. It is ruled by a bad group of people. This group took control of the country in 1962. 

In 2007, people in Burma held protests. These were the first big protests in ten years. The protests were led by monks. The monks wore yellow robes. People called these protests "The Saffron Revolution."  At first, the government let the monks have peaceful meetings. But then the protests got bigger. The government became angry. The army attacked the monks and people who were protesting.

Foreign reporters, who write about news for other countries, were caught and put in jail. One reporter from Japan was killed. His name was Kenji Nagai. He was killed just for being at a protest. The government said that 13 people died. But a soldier who left the army said that many more people were killed.  

This is not new. People in power have always tried to stop people from disagreeing with them.  Long ago, Roman emperors said they were chosen by gods. They wanted to control everything. In Japan, people believe that the emperor is a god. Our president, George W. Bush, talks to a religious leader named Ted Haggard.

There have been other times when governments have been very bad. In 1989, people protested in China.  The government attacked the protesters. Many people died. In the 1990s, there was a terrible killing in Rwanda.  The government helped to kill many people.

Hitler was bad. He killed many Jewish people.

Duke Ellington was a good jazz musician. He played music for a long time. He was good at leading his orchestra. He played the piano, but he was a great composer. He made songs that were complex and had lots of parts. He made songs that showed each musician's skill. He made songs that were both planned and free for the musicians to play new ideas. He made sure the music sounded good together. This made his music very special.

One book about music says Ellington used his voice like an instrument. He did this in a song called "Creole Love Call." He used his voice to make the music interesting. He also made songs that fit each musician's style. "Creole Love Call" is a slow song. It has six parts.

The first part has a voice and wind instruments singing back and forth. The voice starts smooth and then gets rougher.

The second part has a trumpet solo. It plays on the main song idea and uses notes that are not normal.

The third part has a clarinet solo that is high and has a piano part that goes with it.

The fourth part has the whole band play the first part.

The fifth part has the wind instruments play the call and response in a high sound. The brass and drums have a special rhythm.

The sixth part is like the first part, with the voice and wind instruments. The voice sounds rough like a growl.

The song ends with a short part with a voice run and a sound from a trombone.

Ellington used his voice to make the music sound different. He did this in many of his songs.

In another song called "Hot and Bothered," Ellington used a trumpet player and a singer to make interesting sounds. They played back and forth. Ellington also used a trombone player in a song called "It Don't Mean a Thing." He made the trombone sound special.

She always felt like she need something. This want did not go away. It start when she was about 14 years old. She was a teenager. The want was still there three years later, when she was 17. Now she want someone, not a thing. She did not like any boys. Some boys liked her. They try to ask her out, but no one was good enough. She ask herself why. She try to think of a reason for this. She think about it for many years. But she could not find a good answer. So she live her life, always asking herself why.

One day at home was usually calm. Her parents were good and quiet people. They did not fight. They never fight with her either. The only time they fight was when she want to be more independent. She was the daughter of quiet people, but she was very fun. She was also kind, so people liked her.

Today was not a calm day. She walk from room to room to find something to do. She hear a short scream from the kitchen. It was her mother's voice. She run to the kitchen. She worry, "Mom! Mom, what is wrong?" Her mother was on the floor. She was in pain. She say, "Ouch...sweetheart, I...need you to take me to the hospital." Her words were fast and hard to hear. She knew her mother was in a lot of pain. "Okay, Mom. Where should I pick you up?" Her mother point. The daughter was happy she had been strong in her classes. She pick up her mother and put her in the car. She drive to the hospital.

The hospital had the smell of medicine and sickness. It was scary. But she did not feel scared. She was worried about her mother. She take her inside and call for a doctor. Some doctors came and put her mother on a bed. They took her away to look at her. The daughter sat down and waited.

Her mother had fallen off a step stool. She try to get a vase from a high shelf.

This study looked at if eating a "Mediterranean Diet" (Med diet) helps women stay healthy. The Med diet has lots of good food like fruits, vegetables, nuts, and fish.  It has less bad fats and meat.

To measure how much women followed the Med diet, they used a score called "alternate Mediterranean (aMed) diet score". A higher score means they ate more like the Med diet.

Older studies showed the Med diet helps people live longer and have less heart problems. This study looked at if it also helps women avoid strokes.

The study followed 74,886 women for 20 years.  The women answered questions about what they ate every few years. The study used this to see how well they followed the Med diet.

The researchers looked at how many women got heart disease, had a stroke, or died from heart problems. They also looked at other things like how much each woman weighed, if she smoked, and if she took medicine.

The study found that women who ate more like the Med diet had a lower risk of heart disease and stroke. They were less likely to get sick and die from these problems.

In the year 2007, the United States had a big money problem. Many people lost their jobs. Houses became very cheap. Many big companies failed. This problem is still here today. So, we must ask: how did this happen? How can we stop it? 

The money problem was made by bad choices made by people in charge. They made banks give out many loans to people who could not pay them back. This happened because the system for money was not strong enough. 

At the same time, two big companies, Fannie Mae and Freddie Mac, were told to take these bad loans and make them into new things called CDO’s and CDS’. When people could not pay back their loans, the banks had not enough money. They gave the problem to the new things they made. This made the whole country’s money system very sick.

This problem started in the year 1999, when President Clinton was trying to be president again. He wanted more people to like him. So, he made it easier for people to borrow money. This made things worse seven years later. A news reporter, Steven Holmes, said in 1999, "Fannie Mae is being told by the president to give out more loans to poor people. This could be a big problem if the economy gets bad." He was right. 

Many things made the problem worse, including new ways to give out loans. People could borrow money to buy houses more easily. This made many people buy houses, even if they could not really afford them. Prices went up too high, like a bubble. 

Then, the bubble burst. Many people could not pay back their loans. The big banks lost a lot of money. Some banks had to close. Two banks, Fannie and Freddie, had very big problems and the government had to take control of them.

Ah, exposition. That place in your story where you show your talent, fascinating your readers with your words. Or the part where they get bored and leave. Dr. Merlin knows the feeling! She gets frustrated when she writes too much exposition.

Exposition is not your friend.

You already know the writing tip, "Show, don't tell." But Dr. Merlin still writes long passages where nothing happens. Exposition is like a voice in your head that says to tell the reader everything that happened before the story begins. 

Exposition means telling the reader what happened. In movies, one character tells another all the important information. In stories, the author does the telling.

For example, imagine a story where you read that the heroine met her husband at a party, they had a big wedding, and he was murdered in front of her. You wouldn't want to read two pages about this!

Instead, the author should show you the husband's character. Let you see how much he loves his wife through his words and actions. 

Show how the wife changed after meeting him. What did she see in him? How deep was their bond? How did he make her feel?

If the author does this, you will feel sad when he dies and you will connect with the wife more.

In short, you want more detail about the story, not just the basic facts.

As a writer, you need to give your readers more than just the bones of the story.

For example, you might want to tell the reader about a new character who was in the Air Force and now works at a gas station. He's divorced, doesn't have kids, likes to fish, and dreams of owning the gas station. He ate Eggs Benedict for breakfast today.

Tell the reader about all these things!

I saw two news shows from Columbus, Ohio. The first show was NBC 4 this morning (August 13, 2011). The main story was about a man in Ashley, Ohio. He hurt his wife. They did not say her name, but his name was Shad Hostettler. They showed his picture. He looked mean. They talked about this story for about two minutes. They said he hurt his wife many times and was now in jail. I think this was the right amount of time for this story.

The next story was about a man named Travis Buyers. He was 18 years old. He was hurt by a gun in Sharon Woods. He was very sick. No one had caught the person who did this. The police team that fights crime was looking for the person. This story seemed short. I think this was because the man was Black. I have seen that the news shows less about Black people when they are hurt. If a white person is hurt, the news talks a lot about it. 

The next story was about a hole in a helicopter. Someone shot at it with a gun. They said it was a small gun. The police are offering money for information about who shot the helicopter.

The next story was about rain coming this weekend. They said it would be hot. They did not talk about it for very long. They wanted to make you want to watch more.

They also talked about a robbery. A man robbed a store. He was Black and wore a dark shirt. He was tall and thin. They talked a lot about him being Black. 

The last story was about a man named Rene Rodriguez. He was a drug dealer in Texas. He was caught selling a lot of marijuana. He got a long prison sentence. They said 300 months. I do not know why they said that instead of 25 years. They also said he was Hispanic. I do not know why they said this.

Brothers have a strong link. This link has many feelings: love, pride, wish, and meanness. Brothers understand each other better than anyone. They see themselves in their brother. When things are bad, the true link is clear. The feelings are good or bad.  Understanding these feelings means dealing with the results. When you look at your brother, you see yourself, not how others see you, but who you really are. Your actions show your true self.

In "The Scarlet Ibis", two brothers show this link. They have many strong feelings. In a beautiful place, the boys go on a trip that does not work. Big sadness meets strong pride. Only one brother lives. The story shows these feelings through the main character, Doodle, and how he acts. The story also shows the narrator's feelings. This helps us understand the main character and his world.

The main character feels pride. From when he and Doodle first go out together, to their last trip, he feels bad about Doodle. He wanted a brother who could learn things, like running and climbing. He wanted a brother to do things with. These things are hard for Doodle because he is sick. Doodle has a weak heart. It is hard for him to move. This makes the main character sad. He is angry at Doodle. He even thinks about killing Doodle. 

But then Doodle smiles. This makes the main character happy. He loves Doodle.

The human brain is a very complicated thing. It takes in information and makes new ideas. As technology got better, people used new words to explain how the brain works. First, they said it was like a wax tablet. Then they said it was like paper. Then they said it was like a book. Now, many people say it is like a computer. But remember, these words are just ways to think about the brain. They do not tell us everything.

Information comes into the brain from our senses. Our eyes, ears, skin, and tongue feel things and turn them into signals the brain can use. The brain uses these signals to make sense of the world. It does this in two ways. 

One way is called "bottom-up" processing. It starts with small pieces of information and puts them together to make a bigger picture. For example, when you see a black box on a white background, your brain sees the color black, the shape of the box, and where the edges are. It puts all these pieces together to know that you are seeing a box. 

The other way is called "top-down" processing. This uses what you already know to understand new information. If you see a black box, your brain might already know what a box is, so it can recognize it faster.

The brain also has a filter that decides what is important. It pays attention to things that are important and ignores things that are not. For example, when you walk down the street, you see many things. But your brain only pays attention to the things that are important, like a stop sign or a friend's face.

The brain stores information in different ways. There is short-term memory and long-term memory. Short-term memory holds information for a short time, like 20 seconds. Long-term memory stores information for a long time.

There are many ways to think about how the brain stores information. Some people say it is like a network of ideas, where each idea is connected to other ideas.

Aldous Huxley show the bad thing of new technology and the system of business in his book *Brave New World*. His book show a bad future. The people in this book care more about being part of a group than being a single person. They are told to only think about being happy. The people are like pieces in a game. They live in a world where only one way of thinking is allowed. The people in charge are called the World Controllers.  

If you look at the book using a way of thinking called Marxist theism, you can see that Huxley is worried about these new things. Words like "same" and "thing" are used a lot in Marxism. These words show that Huxley thinks there are problems with the way business was going in his time.

Huxley uses a idea from Marx called "false knowing". This means that people don't know how money really works. They are only interested in getting more things for themselves. The people in charge control the workers and keep them happy.

The people in *Brave New World* are trained to want things, to spend money, and to be happy. The World Controller controls them. This is a kind of power called "hegemony". The people at the bottom don't know they are being controlled. The people at the top know but don't do anything about it.

In *Brave New World*, people don't really know each other. They don't have deep feelings. Maybe Huxley is saying that technology and business make people forget how to feel and be themselves. Love and strong feelings don't exist. People only talk about each other's looks. The people in each group accept their place in society. This shows that capitalism makes people follow rules and not think for themselves.

I go to school at University Park. I have been a student here for about two and a half years. Getting around campus can be hard. My first year, I lived in an East Halls dorm. This is far from most of the buildings. It take a long time to walk to classes in buildings like Willard, which is near the center of campus. It can take up to 25 minutes to walk there, even longer if the weather is bad.

I talked to a person who went to school here a few years ago. He said that the East Halls dorms used to be very far from the rest of the school. There was a lot of empty space between them. Now, there are new buildings, sports fields, and apartments there. The campus is getting bigger, and it is harder to get around.

What is the best way to get around campus? I think it is by bike. But just having bikes is not enough. Students need to ride them, and the campus needs to be made for bikes.

I talked to a friend who started riding a bike again. He said he does not know why he stopped. He said, “Bikes are great! It is the best way to get around.”  Riding a bike is good for your body, and it is fast. You can go far on a bike with just a little food.

I live off campus now, just as far from the center of campus as some dorms. The best thing I did this year was buy a bike. I have class in Thomas building, which is far from my house. It takes 25 minutes to walk there, but only 5 minutes on a bike.

The road to Thomas building is not always safe to ride a bike on. But walking is not good for me because I am too busy. If I did not have a bike, I would have to walk. Walking to Thomas every day would take me over two and a half hours every week. That is too much time.

In pursuing an education in social work, I intend to follow a career path with the Division of Family and Children Services to help children who have been abused or neglected; and to provide support for troubled families. Values that I can provide to the social work field include the following: service, respect, ethical nature, commitment to help improve relationships between others and to improve myself professionally to remain competent in my field. These core values are not just important to social workers; they are important to me personally. 

	I have always wanted to help others, but I was unsure of the career path that I wanted to follow. Throughout my years in high school and college, I saw many individuals flee from their problems in denial and a few used coping mechanisms that were less than ideal. Because of situations that I have witnessed, I chose to pursue a Bachelor’s degree in Psychology. Still unsure of a career path, I decided to take a break once I graduated from Piedmont College in 2009. One day that summer, I visited a friend who introduced me to a sixteen year-old boy sitting nervously on her couch. She explained to me why he was visiting: to escape his abusive parents. The next day, I learned that he had called the police to his parent’s residence. To see if I could help in any way, I drove over to his parents’ house. Once there, I privately explained my concerns to the police and told them I had just graduated with a degree in Psychology from Piedmont College. The police requested that I talk to the parents since there was nothing that the law could do for the teenager. When I questioned the parents about the situation, they seemed nervous and used excuses to describe their son’s “manipulative” behavior for involving outside sources to resolve “simple” disputes. After this particular experience, I began to seriously consider a career in social work to help children with “simple” disputes among family members.

	Another value that is important for the field of social work is social justice. As a society, we claim that the individual is important and we mourn those that we have lost. The concept of the “individual” that society holds is more a follower of archaic traditions than actual uniqueness. So, if society mourns lost individuals, then why do we strive to be similar to “everyone else?” I am an individual and do not enjoy placing limitations on myself to be similar to others. Throughout my years at high school and college, I protested against social injustice whenever I could: coloring my hair unnatural colors, wearing clothing that fit my personality, piercing my ears past the traditional set, declaring my involvement with GSBA (Gay Straight Bisexual Alliance), fighting against both racism and discrimination whenever I witnessed it, etc. I believe in social justice and I will continue to protest against social injustice.

The following paper addresses the Biological and Sociocultural models in relation to the disorder insomnia. The biological model focuses on genetic information that is inherited as well as medical aspects of health. The Sociocultural models look at environmental relationships and their applications to race, ethnicity, demographics, and socioeconomic status. The following review of insomnia looks at these models and explains each piece of research chosen to relate to and to better explain the models. The explanations of the research and their findings are then critiqued to mention their specific strengths and weaknesses.

A sleep disorder can be characterized as a primary sleep disorder, a sleep disorder related to another mental disorder, or a sleep disorder related to other issues. The Primary sleep disorders are Dyssonmias or Parasomnias while sleep disorders related to another mental disorder are related to an Axis I or Axis II disorder. Other categories of sleep disorders can be due to medical complications or the intake of a substance. The Dyssomnias are: Primary Insomnia, Primary Hypersomnia, Narcolepsy, Breathing- Related Sleep Disorder, Circadian Rhythm Sleep Disorder, and Dyssomnia Not Otherwise Specified (NOS). While Primary Insomnia is a complication in adequate or maintained sleep, Primary Hypersomnia is a difficulty in staying awake, both for at least a one month period of time. Narcolepsy involves cataplexy and/ or automatic REM. While Dyssonmias focus on initiating and remaining asleep, the Parasomnias are sleep disorders associated with behavioral abnormalities and/ or physiological occurrences. Parasomnias are Nightmare Disorder, Sleep Terror Disorder, Sleepwalking Disorder, and Parasomnias Not Otherwise Specified. The sleep disorders related to another mental disorder involve sleep difficulties due to Axis I (Clinical Disorders) or Axis II (Personality Disorders or Mental Retardation). The following review focuses on insomnia, and somewhat on primary sleep disorders in general in relation to the biological and sociocultural models.

	 The biological model of sleep disorders focuses on genes, heritable factors, and physiologically acquired aspect of sleep disorders. Neurons in the hypothalamus containing orexin are responsible for the regulation of sleep and wakefulness. This study experimented with mice and found that there are phenotypic GABAB receptors on the orexin neurons which are specifically responsible for sleep/ wake states. The activation of the GABAA receptor induces responses that promote sleep. If it is inhibited from firing, this can cause reduced anxiety and induce sleep. The GABAB agonist (baclofen) increased sleep time (Matsuki et al., 2009). Such results imply that the animal models of mice can be generalized to studies in humans. This shows that there is a genetic and environmental basis for the physical GABAB receptor in humans. A problem or absence with this receptor could alter the ability of one to have adequate sleep without medication. The sociocultural implication of this study is that if the phenotype was inherited, this could regulate sleep, and an alteration of the receptor would naturally disturb sleep for an individual. This would negatively impact aspects of life such as school, career, and every day events that involve monotonous tasks and focus.

This paper covers three areas of Central Auditory Processing Disorder (CAPD). First, a brief definition of the disorder is provided. Next, diagnosis is explained, with common characteristics, or “red flags”. Finally, the paper concludes with ways that a teacher in a mainstreamed classroom environment can assist a student with CAPD.

	Central Auditory Processing Disorder (CAPD), or Auditory Processing Disorder (APD) “refers to the efficiency and effectiveness by which the central nervous system (CNS) utilizes auditory information. Narrowly defined, (C)AP refers to the perceptual processing of auditory information in the CNS and the neurobiologic activity that underlies that processing and gives rise to electrophysiologic auditory potentials” (American Speech-Language-Hearing Association, 2005), meaning it is a disorder wherein the central nervous system (i.e. the brain) cannot properly process things that are heard. People with CAPD can hear normally, and are therefore not considered “hearing impaired”; rather, the area of the brain that translates what we hear, separating words or differentiating conversation from background noise does not function as it typically should. 

	The earliest mention of the disorder that became CAPD is from the mid-1950s, called “auditory imperception” (American Speech-Language-Hearing Association, 2005) when researchers were evaluating children with communicative disorders. The Italian research team of Bocca, Calearo, and Cassinari began developing tests for these children in 1954; in 1961, Kimura “introduced dichotic testing and formulated a model to explain the physiology of the CANS underlying dichotic perception” (American Speech-Language-Hearing Association, 2005). A national conference was held in 1977 that stimulated research on children with CAPD. 

	CAPD manifests itself in multiple ways: the person suffering may not be able to localize or hear sound in space; may have difficulty discriminating between two or more “acoustic events” (sound occurrences); may not be able to recognize sound patterns; may not be able to differentiate changes in speech (like detecting sarcasm based on change of voice); one sound may be blocked by a subsequent sound; may not have the ability to synthesize sound clues (that is, interpret in a meaningful way that they can then act upon); and may not be able to determine the sequence in which auditory information is presented (Ferre).

	In order to diagnose CAPD, the patient must be screened with “systematic observation of listening behavior and/or performance on tests of auditory function”, which may be conducted by “audiologists, SLPs, psychologists, and others using a variety of measures that evaluate auditory-related skills” (American Speech-Language-Hearing Association, 2005). This may include questionnaires and surveys, observation of auditory behaviors, including how the patient responds to certain stimuli. There is, at this time, no one tool or test that is used consistently to a high rate of diagnostic success, and there is no known cause for the disorder. Many tests used present the patient with multiple, simultaneous auditory stimuli and then ask for them to differentiate certain items, like a series of words or numbers. More advanced tests include recording acoustic signals within the ear and measuring the responses to the signals.

The play Twelfth Night seems to say that although disguise is in fact useful in perpetrating long bouts of deception, in the end a person must reject that newly formed guise, or else risk losing themselves forever in the process. A big problem with ending a deception, however, is that one may find themselves alienated in the process. Therefore, in the end, one must decide between one’s own self preservation, or the preservation of relationships with those around them. For although some will respond neutrally to discovering that they’ve been tricked, still others will not take the deception so lightly, and will be likely be offended by the whole charade.
The topic of deception in gender role reversal is especially problematic, because it brings up many side issues, perhaps the most important one being, why? Why does the subject feel the need to shirk their own identity and take up a disguise in the form of the opposite gender? In Viola’s case, it is obviously a form of self protection.: “I’ll bring you to a captain in this town/ Where lie my maiden weeds, by whose gentle help/ I was preserved to serve this noble count…” (5.1.247-249)
Having newly arrived in a foreign land, Viola feels it necessary to pretend to be a man to protect herself from would be attackers. Viola’s plan works, but it also alienates her from the women around her, cutting her off from an important support system. To make matters worse, she is apparently so convincing at appearing to be a man that Olivia confuses her with Sebastian, and in effect falls in love with her. “Whither, my lord?
